    {
      "note_no": "5",
      "note": "The very concept of \"time\" is meaningless in relation to God, who is timeless and infinite: cf. note 63 on the last sentence of 22:47 - \"in thy Sustainer's sight a day is like a thousand years of your reckoning\": in other words, a day, or an aeon, or a thousand years, or fifty thousand years are alike to Him, having an apparent reality only within the created world and none with the Creator. And since in the hereafter time will cease to have a meaning for man as well, it is irrelevant to ask as to \"when\" the evildoers will be chastised and the righteous given their due."
